# React Graph AI — Graph Memory Active

This project uses React Graph AI for token-optimized React/Next.js context.
The MCP server provides a behavioral graph of this codebase.

## Rules

### Always call get_minimal_context first
Before answering ANY question about this codebase — bugs, features,
refactors, or architecture — call get_minimal_context with the query.
Do NOT read source files directly. The graph returns structural context
at 10-100x fewer tokens than reading files.

### Always call get_impact_analysis before changing shared components
Before editing any component used by other components, call
get_impact_analysis. If impact is HIGH, warn the developer first.

### Use trace_state_flow for state and data flow questions
When asked about state, re-renders, or data flow, call trace_state_flow.
Do not trace state manually by reading files.

### Use get_component_tree for hierarchy questions
When asked about component structure or render relationships, call
get_component_tree instead of reading files.

### Use list_components to discover the codebase
When you need to know what components exist before querying a specific one,
call list_components first.

## Workflow

Developer: "Fix the login bug in Navbar"
1. get_minimal_context("Navbar login") — get structural context
2. get_impact_analysis("Navbar") — check blast radius
3. Make the targeted fix using only what the graph returned
4. Do not open Navbar.tsx or any related file directly

## Token cost reference

| Task                  | Tool                  | Tokens    |
|-----------------------|-----------------------|-----------|
| Fix a bug             | get_minimal_context   | ~200-500  |
| Refactor a component  | get_minimal_context + get_impact_analysis | ~400-800 |
| Trace data flow       | trace_state_flow      | ~200-400  |
| Explore structure     | get_component_tree    | ~300-600  |
| Direct file read      | (avoid)               | ~2k-20k   |
